    "narrative": "Our highest-upside play for today\u2019s slate is **Lawrence Butler**, whose score of 73.43 is bolstered significantly by an advantageous matchup against Michael Wacha. While his spot at the bottom of the order carries a slight penalty, the combination of a favorable park factor (+10%) and an excellent dynamic platoon edge (+13%) makes him a must-start. Similarly, **Daulton Varsho** (70.72) and **Tyler Freeman** (70.26) present as elite starts. **Tyler Freeman** specifically benefits from the highest SP skill boost on our roster (+19%) against Brandon Williamson, with wind blowing out providing an extra layer of optimism for his offensive output.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the optimizer involved the exclusion of **Matt Chapman**. With a score of 42.56, he narrowly missed the starting cut; while his order placement at #2 provides a structural boost, the matchup against Cristopher S\u00e1nchez\u2014combined with a 40% rain risk\u2014devalued his floor significantly compared to our preferred starters. We are also monitoring **Bryson Stott** (51.79) closely, as he occupies a lineup spot despite the same 40% rain risk. While he faces the formidable Logan Webb, he remains in our lineup because the game environment\u2014specifically the slow delivery of the opposing pitcher\u2014offers a high probability of stolen base opportunities, keeping him marginally viable despite the weather concerns.\n\nThe rest of our primary core remains rock solid. **Cal Raleigh** (67.47), **Jonathan Aranda** (67.67), and **Will Smith** (67.60) are our anchors, all delivering high-efficiency scores driven by strong batting order placement and favorable matchups against mid-rotation arms like Taj Bradley and Gavin Williams. We are keeping **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Taylor Ward** in the mix for their park-adjusted potential against Peter Lambert, though we are wary of their bottom-of-the-order usage. As we await official lineup confirmation for **Yainer Diaz**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, their projected scores suggest they are safe pivots regardless of minor fluctuations in their batted order position.",
